{{Infobox government agency | name = Brunei History Centre | native_name = {{lang|ms|Pusat Sejarah Brunei}} | type = [[Government department]] | seal = | logo = | formed = {{startdate|1982|01|26|df=y}} | jurisdiction = [[Government of Brunei]] | headquarters = Jalan James Pearce, [[Bandar Seri Begawan]], [[Brunei]] | coordinates = {{coord|4|53|30.6|N|114|56|30.0|E|region:BN_type:landmark}} | chief1_name = [[Mohd. Jamil Al-Sufri]] | chief1_position = Principal of the Brunei History Centre | parent_department = [[Ministry of Culture, Youth and Sports (Brunei)|Ministry of Culture, Youth and Sports]] | website = http://www.pusat-sejarah.gov.bn }}
The '''Brunei History Centre''' ({{Lang-ms|Pusat Sejarah Brunei}}, abbreviated as ''{{Abbr|PSB|Pusat Sejarah Brunei}}'') is a government institution which conducts research, documentation, publication and dissemination on matters pertaining to the [[history of Brunei]].<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.pusat-sejarah.gov.bn/Themed/eng-foreword.htm|title=Brunei History Centre|last=|first=|date=|website=www.pusat-sejarah.gov.bn|archive-url=|archive-date=|dead-url=|access-date=2017-12-20}}</ref> It was established in 1982 by the consent of [[Sultan Hassanal Bolkiah]] as an institute of historical research on Brunei for the benefit of the Bruneian people.<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.pusat-sejarah.gov.bn/Themed/eng-brief_history.htm|title=Brief History|last=|first=|date=|website=www.pusat-sejarah.gov.bn|archive-url=|archive-date=|dead-url=|access-date=2017-12-20}}</ref> The head of Brunei History Centre is a Principal ({{Lang-ms|Pengetua}}), which is held by [[Mohd. Jamil Al-Sufri]].<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.pusat-sejarah.gov.bn/Themed/eng-email.htm|title=Email List|last=|first=|date=|website=www.pusat-sejarah.gov.bn|archive-url=|archive-date=|dead-url=|access-date=2017-12-20}}</ref> It is a government department under the Ministry of Culture, Youth and Sports.<ref name=":0">{{Cite web|url=http://www.pusat-sejarah.gov.bn/Themed/sejarah.htm|title=Sejarah Ringkas|last=|first=|date=|website=www.pusat-sejarah.gov.bn|archive-url=|archive-date=|dead-url=|access-date=2017-12-20}}</ref>
== History == The Brunei History Centre was established on 26 January 1982 by the Consent of His Majesty Sultan Hassanal Bolkiah to conduct research and dissemination on the history of Brunei for the benefit of the people in the country.<ref name=":0" /><ref name=":1">{{Cite news|url=http://mediapermata.com.bn/rombongan-ubd-lawat-pusat-sejarah/|title=Rombongan UBD lawat Pusat Sejarah – Media Permata Online|date=2017-10-19|work=Media Permata Online|access-date=2017-12-20|language=en-US}}</ref> Initially, the Centre was housed in the [[Bandar Seri Begawan Library|main branch]] of the [[Dewan Bahasa dan Pustaka Library]] at [[Jalan Elizabeth II]], [[Bandar Seri Begawan]].<ref name=":0" /><ref name=":1" /> In 1985, it was moved to the building at [[Jalan Stoney]] which was formerly the then [[Ministry of Education (Brunei)|Department of Education]] ({{Lang-ms|Jabatan Pelajaran}}). In 1988, the Centre finally moved to the present building at Jalan James Pearce.<ref name=":0" /><ref name=":1" />
